# ── adoreview configuration ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill it in. Bun loads `.env` automatically.
# `.env` is gitignored — never commit it.

# Your Azure DevOps organization, i.e. the <org> in https://dev.azure.com/<org>
ADO_ORG=your-org

# The ADO project whose pull requests you want to review
ADO_PROJECT=Your Project

# Where your local git clones live. adoreview reads file contents and diffs
# from clones you ALREADY have here — it never fetches file content over the
# API. Defaults to ~/Projects if unset.
# ADO_PROJECTS_ROOT=/Users/you/Projects

# Port for the local server (default 4680).
# PORT=4680

# ── Authentication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# By DEFAULT you need NO secret here. adoreview mints a short-lived Microsoft
# Entra token from your existing Azure CLI session — just run `az login` once.
# Conditional Access / MFA apply as normal and nothing is written to disk.
#
# Set a Personal Access Token below ONLY if you cannot use the az CLI (e.g. a
# headless box or CI). Create it in ADO → User settings → Personal access
# tokens, scoped to:  Code (Read)  ·  Pull Request Threads (Read & Write).
# It is sent via HTTP Basic and is never logged. Treat it like a password;
# this file is gitignored, so keep your PAT here and nowhere else.
# ADO_PAT=
